Essex, England":"英国艾可達根哈姆","lifeSummary":"当Samuel Hubbard于1466年7月1日出生在英国英格兰艾可達根哈姆时，他的父亲Thomas Hubbard25岁，母亲Eleanor Atchurch51岁。他于大约1485年与Katherine Wright在英国艾可達根哈姆结婚。他们至少是1个儿子和1个女儿的父母。他去世于1520年在英国艾可達根哈姆享年54岁，埋葬在英国艾可達根哈姆。"},"hr":{"1 Jul 1466–1520":"1. srpnja 1466.–1520.","1466–1520":"1466–1520.","1469–1558":"1469–1558","1487–1560":"1487–1560","1516–1587":"1516.–1587","1441–1478":"1441–1478.","1415–1466":"1415–1466","1 Jul 1466":"1. srpnja 1466.","after 1 July 1466":"nakon 1. srpnja 1466.","1560":"1560","22 February 1487":"22. veljače 1487.","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","1469":"1469","1478":"1478.","1587":"1587","1466":"1466","1520":"1520.","1487":"1487","1441":"1441","about 1485":"oko 1485.","1516":"1516.","Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England":"Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England","Of Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, Engleska, United Kingdom","Dagenham Essex England":"Dagenham, Essex, Engleska, United Kingdom","Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, England"},"cs":{"1 Jul 1466–1520":"1. července 1466–1520","1466–1520":"1466–1520","1469–1558":"1469–1558","1487–1560":"1487–1560","1516–1587":"1516–1587","1441–1478":"1441–1478","1415–1466":"1415–1466","1 Jul 1466":"1. července 1466","after 1 July 1466":"po 1. července 1466","1560":"1560","22 February 1487":"22. února 1487","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","1469":"1469","1478":"1478","1587":"1587","1466":"1466","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1441":"1441","about 1485":"okolo 1485","1516":"1516","Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England":"Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, Anglie","Of Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, Anglie, United Kingdom","Dagenham Essex England":"Dagenham, Essex, Anglie, United Kingdom","Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, Anglie"},"da":{"1 Jul 1466–1520":"1. juli 1466–1520","1466–1520":"1466–1520","1469–1558":"1469–1558","1487–1560":"1487–1560","1516–1587":"1516–1587","1441–1478":"1441–1478","1415–1466":"1415–1466","1 Jul 1466":"1. juli 1466","after 1 July 1466":"efter 1. juli 1466","1560":"1560","22 February 1487":"22. februar 1487","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","1469":"1469","1478":"1478","1587":"1587","1466":"1466","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1441":"1441","about 1485":"omkring 1485","1516":"1516","Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England":"Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England","Of Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dagenham Essex England":"Dagenham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, England"},"nl":{"1 Jul 1466–1520":"1 juli 1466–1520","1466–1520":"1466–1520","1469–1558":"1469–1558","1487–1560":"1487–1560","1516–1587":"1516–1587","1441–1478":"1441–1478","1415–1466":"1415–1466","1 Jul 1466":"1 juli 1466","after 1 July 1466":"na 1 juli 1466","1560":"1560","22 February 1487":"22 februari 1487","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","1469":"1469","1478":"1478","1587":"1587","1466":"1466","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1441":"1441","about 1485":"circa 1485","1516":"1516","Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England":"Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England","Of Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Dagenham Essex England":"Dagenham, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, England"},"en":{"1 Jul 1466–1520":"1 July 1466–1520","1466–1520":"1466–1520","1469–1558":"1469–1558","1487–1560":"1487–1560","1516–1587":"1516–1587","1441–1478":"1441–1478","1415–1466":"1415–1466","1 Jul 1466":"1 July 1466","after 1 July 1466":"after 1 July 1466","1560":"1560","22 February 1487":"22 February 1487","1415":"1415","1558":"1558","1469":"1469","1478":"1478","1587":"1587","1466":"1466","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1441":"1441","about 1485":"about 1485","1516":"1516","Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England":"Kelvedon Hatch, Essex, England","Of Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dagenham Essex England":"Dagenham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dagenham, Essex, England":"Dagenham, Essex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hubbard","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: of Norman origin, from the Norman French personal name   Hubert   (ancient Germanic <i>Hugibert</i>, composed of elements meaning ‘mind, spirit’ and ‘bright’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Hubbartt","meanings":["English: variant of   Hubbard  ."]},{"name":"Hubert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Armand, Normand, Olivier, Adlore, Alphonse, Andre, Benoit, Camil, Camille, Fernand.","German, Dutch, English, French, Walloon, Breton, Polish, Czech, Slovak, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. The name was borne by an 8th-century Christian saint, bishop of Maastricht, who was adopted as the patron of hunters, and helped to increase the popularity of the personal name, especially in the Low Countries.","History: Jean-François-Barthélemi Hubert from Granville in Manche, France, married Félicité Arsenault in Havre-Aubert, QC, in 1801. Nicolas Hubert <i>dit</i> Lacroix from France married Marguerite Landreau in France <i>c.</i> 1653, died in Montreal, QC, in 1687. René Hubert from Paris, France, married Françoise (de) Lacroix in Quebec City, QC, in 1669. Pierre-Paul Hébert/Hubert from France married Suzanne Laporte in QC <i>c.</i> 1716. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of South Carolina."]},{"name":"Hubbart","meanings":["English (Durham): variant of   Hubbard  ."]},{"name":"Hobart","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   Hubbard  , though Middle English <i>Hobert</i> and <i>Hoberd</i> could represent Anglo-Norman French forms of <i>Osbert</i>, with loss of <i>-s-</i>. Compare   Opie  , which was a pet form of <i>Osbert</i>, and   Hobby  , which might sometimes have been as well."]}]},{"name":"Samuel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name (Hebrew <i>Shemuel</i>), possibly meaning ‘He (God) has hearkened’ (presumably to the prayers of a mother for a son). It may also be understood as a contracted form of Hebrew <i>sha'ulme'el</i> meaning ‘asked of God’. In the case of Samuel the son of Hannah, this would be more in keeping with his mother's statement ‘Because I have asked him of the Lord’ (1 Samuel 1:20). Living in the 11th century  bc , Samuel was a Hebrew judge and prophet of the greatest historical importance, who established the Hebrew monarchy, anointing as king both Saul and, later, David. In the Authorized Version two books of the Old Testament are named after him, although in Roman Catholic and Orthodox versions of the Bible they are known as the first and second Book of Kings. The story of Samuel being called by God while still a child serving in the house of Eli the priest (1 Samuel 3) is of great vividness and has moved countless generations. In England and America the name was particularly popular among the 16th-century Puritans and among Nonconformists from the 17th to the 19th century. It became fashionable again in the 1990s."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Samuel Hubbard was born on 1 July 1466, in Dagenham, Essex, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Hubbard, was 25 and his mother, Eleanor Atchurch, was 51. He married Katherine Wright about 1485, in Dagenham, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1520, in Dagenham, Essex, England, at the age of 54, and was buried in Dagenham, Essex, England."},"et":{"1 Jul 1466–1520":"1. juuli 1466–1520","1466–1520":"1466–1520","1469–1558":"1469–1558","1487–1560":"1487–1560","1516–1587":"1516–1587","1441–1478":"1441–1478","1415–1466":"1415–1466","1 Jul 1466":"1. juuli 1466","after 1 July 1466":"pärast 1. juulit 1466","1560":"1560","22 February 1487":"22. veebruar 1487","1415":"1415","15